The station was opened in August 1908 by the German consortium Anatolia-Baghdad Corporation.
Germany, a latecomer to the imperial game, had ambitions to dominate the Middle East through this railroad that stretched to Damascus, Baghdad, and beyond into what is now Saudi Arabia.
However, the ambitions of this imperial Germany failed during World War I.
Their railroads were attacked by Lawrence of Arabia and his irregular Arabs.
